WEBVTT

00:13.560 --> 00:15.560
- ("Before I Ever Met You" by BANKS plays)
- (vocalizing)

00:21.730 --> 00:26.850
(vocalizing)

00:28.560 --> 00:31.060
(vocalizing)

00:31.150 --> 00:33.150
(instruments join in)

00:45.770 --> 00:51.560
♪ Everyone knows I'm right
about one thing ♪

00:51.670 --> 00:55.460
♪ You and I don't work out ♪

00:55.540 --> 00:57.460
(vocalizing)

00:57.540 --> 00:59.960
♪ You bring out the mean in me ♪

01:00.040 --> 01:03.170
♪ I bring out your insecurities ♪

01:03.250 --> 01:07.420
♪ You know what I am talking about ♪

01:07.500 --> 01:09.670
♪ ♪

01:22.460 --> 01:25.960
(vocalizing)

01:39.290 --> 01:41.290
(music stops)

01:44.420 --> 01:45.960
What?

01:50.000 --> 01:52.790
Nothing.

02:04.130 --> 02:06.130
(birds chirping)

02:15.960 --> 02:17.960
- (music resumes)
- (vocalizing)

02:28.130 --> 02:31.960
(vocalizing continues)

02:32.040 --> 02:34.040
(song ends)

02:39.040 --> 02:42.420
Alexa, play "Old MacDonald."

02:42.500 --> 02:46.000
- (Alexa chimes, song plays)
- ♪ Old MacDonald had a farm ♪

02:46.090 --> 02:49.000
♪ E-I-E-I-O ♪

02:49.090 --> 02:52.000
- ♪ And on his farm he had some ducks ♪
- Trixie!

02:52.090 --> 02:53.790
♪ E-I-E-I-O ♪

02:53.880 --> 02:55.500
- (doorbell rings)
- ♪ With a quack quack here ♪

02:55.590 --> 02:57.170
- ♪ And a quack quack there ♪
- Trixie, I'm not kidding.

02:57.250 --> 02:59.630
♪ Here a quack, there a quack,
everywhere a quack quack ♪

02:59.710 --> 03:01.500
- ♪ Old MacDonald had a farm ♪
- Hey. -Hey.

03:01.590 --> 03:02.670
MELINDA: Turn it off.

03:02.750 --> 03:04.380
♪ E-I-E-I-O ♪

03:04.460 --> 03:07.340
♪ And on his farm he had some cows ♪

03:07.420 --> 03:09.750
♪ E-I-E-I-O ♪

03:09.840 --> 03:11.960
- I'm so, so sorry I'm late, Mr. Van Allen.
- ♪ With a moo moo here... ♪

03:12.040 --> 03:14.790
It's okay. Melinda's…
It's okay, Melinda's still getting ready.

03:14.880 --> 03:17.790
♪ Old MacDonald had a farm ♪

03:17.880 --> 03:20.710
- ♪ E-I-E-I-O. ♪
- Alexa, stop!

03:20.790 --> 03:22.340
- (Alexa chimes, music stops)
- (laughs quietly)

03:22.420 --> 03:25.250
Don't play that shit ever again, please.

03:26.420 --> 03:27.670
Vic, can you come here?

03:27.750 --> 03:28.920
What?

03:29.000 --> 03:30.500
I need your help.

03:30.590 --> 03:33.710
Alexa, play "Old MacDonald" again.

03:33.790 --> 03:36.040
- (Alexa chimes, song plays)
- ♪ Old MacDonald had a farm ♪

03:36.130 --> 03:38.670
Trixie, you're going to drive
your mom crazy, you know that?

03:38.750 --> 03:41.000
I know.

03:41.090 --> 03:42.920
- (chuckles)
- ♪ And on his farm he had some ducks ♪

03:43.000 --> 03:45.290
- ♪ E-I-E-I-O ♪
- VIC: Have a seat.

03:45.380 --> 03:46.670
- ♪ With a quack quack here ♪
- Hey, Trixie.

03:46.750 --> 03:49.460
♪ And a quack quack there,
here a quack… ♪

03:49.540 --> 03:51.460
(song continues low in background)

03:51.540 --> 03:54.090
(Vic sighs)

03:55.170 --> 03:57.290
Don't look at the mess. Look at me.

03:57.380 --> 03:58.960
Yes.

03:59.040 --> 04:00.710
I don't know, I just...

04:00.790 --> 04:04.540
Should I wear this or this?

04:04.630 --> 04:06.630
Um…

04:07.630 --> 04:09.670
No? You don't like either?

04:09.750 --> 04:11.380
No, I'm just thinking.

04:13.500 --> 04:14.750
Hmm?

04:15.840 --> 04:17.959
I think you look beautiful
in the dress you have on.

04:19.130 --> 04:20.750
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

04:22.960 --> 04:24.500
Okay.

04:25.590 --> 04:28.000
(Melinda sighs)

04:28.090 --> 04:30.000
With what shoe?

04:30.090 --> 04:32.210
The black shoes I got you in New York.

04:34.670 --> 04:36.500
Okay.

04:38.250 --> 04:40.130
Go get them.

04:42.250 --> 04:43.630
Please.

04:43.710 --> 04:44.960
(softly): Sure.

05:00.840 --> 05:03.460
Do you know I love you?

05:10.170 --> 05:12.130
Come on.

05:12.210 --> 05:13.960
Let's go.

05:14.040 --> 05:16.670
("Sneakin' Sally Through the Alley"
by Robert Palmer playing)

05:20.670 --> 05:24.170
- ♪ Sneakin' Sally through the alley ♪
- (loud crowd chatter)

05:26.630 --> 05:29.460
- ♪ Trying to keep her out of sight ♪
- MAN: Enjoy.

05:30.500 --> 05:32.540
♪ Sneakin' Sally through the alley... ♪

05:32.630 --> 05:35.540
We asked her
and she chose public school.

05:35.630 --> 05:37.500
- You let her choose?
- VIC: Mm-hmm.

05:37.590 --> 05:39.500
- She's six.
- I was kicked out

05:39.590 --> 05:42.750
of so many schools growing up,
I'm just grateful she wants an education.

05:43.750 --> 05:45.910
You aren't worried about
competition for college?

05:45.910 --> 05:46.540
VIC: College?

05:46.630 --> 05:49.590
The kid's brilliant. The worst thing
we could do is send her to college.

05:49.670 --> 05:51.710
(Melinda laughs)

05:51.790 --> 05:54.210
- ♪ ♪
- (crowd chatter)

06:04.040 --> 06:05.380
Joel.

06:08.880 --> 06:11.790
BARTENDER:
So, uh, how you doing tonight?

06:12.750 --> 06:14.210
Hmm?

06:14.290 --> 06:17.000
No, I was just asking
how you're doing tonight.

06:18.090 --> 06:19.960
I'll let you know
after a few more of these.

06:23.250 --> 06:27.500
♪ Oh, when up pops the queen ♪

06:27.590 --> 06:30.170
♪ Trying to double talk,
get myself in trouble talk ♪

06:30.250 --> 06:32.460
♪ Catching myself in lies ♪

06:34.170 --> 06:37.340
♪ Catch myself in lies ♪

06:37.420 --> 06:42.250
♪ Mama just looked at me
as if I was, ah, crazy... ♪

06:42.340 --> 06:44.340
(band playing "Walking Blues")

06:50.750 --> 06:55.210
♪ I woke up this mornin',
lookin' round for my shoes, yeah ♪

06:55.290 --> 06:58.290
♪ You know that I have
them old walkin' blues... ♪

06:58.380 --> 07:00.090
JOEL: Whoo.

07:00.170 --> 07:02.170
(low music playing)

07:12.210 --> 07:16.420
♪ He got Elgin movement
from his head down to his toes ♪

07:16.500 --> 07:20.590
♪ I bet he can make himself a dollar
anywhere he goes ♪

07:20.670 --> 07:22.420
♪ He got the Elgin movement... ♪

07:22.500 --> 07:24.500
(low music plays)

07:36.340 --> 07:38.340
♪ ♪

07:48.920 --> 07:50.920
(rock riff plays)

08:00.210 --> 08:02.210
(low chatter)

08:03.340 --> 08:04.960
Yo.

08:05.040 --> 08:08.420
Yo. How's it going?

08:08.500 --> 08:10.920
I'm getting a lot
of cleavage action tonight.

08:11.000 --> 08:13.170
- Hmm. I see that.
- (laughing)

08:15.000 --> 08:16.840
MARY: Is that Joel with Melinda?

08:17.920 --> 08:19.540
VIC: Yeah.

08:20.590 --> 08:23.460
They've really hit it off
in a short amount of time, haven't they?

08:23.540 --> 08:26.000
I guess they have.

08:28.710 --> 08:31.170
(laughs) Hello, Mr. Boring.

08:31.250 --> 08:33.000
Why don't you dance?

08:33.090 --> 08:35.250
I'd hate to ruin your evening.

08:42.539 --> 08:46.500
You know he's only here because she asked
Jess and Grant to invite him here.

08:46.590 --> 08:48.290
She can invite whoever she wants.

08:48.380 --> 08:50.290
Vic...

08:50.380 --> 08:51.880
they fucking?

08:51.960 --> 08:53.670
- Should we ask them?
- Vic.

08:56.590 --> 08:58.500
They're friends.

08:58.590 --> 09:00.000
Aren't they just.

09:00.090 --> 09:02.000
(clicks tongue, inhales deeply)

09:02.090 --> 09:04.420
- I'm gonna just blurt it out, okay?
- Okay.

09:04.500 --> 09:05.880
A few of us are concerned.

09:05.960 --> 09:08.790
- You're concerned?
- Yes.

09:08.880 --> 09:10.210
That they're fucking?

09:10.290 --> 09:11.540
(laughs quietly)

09:11.630 --> 09:13.960
What if your concerns aren't my concerns?

09:16.040 --> 09:18.670
Look, you adore her and everyone knows it.

09:20.340 --> 09:22.590
- I love her.
- She loves you, too.

09:23.670 --> 09:25.840
You're good, Vic.

09:26.630 --> 09:29.380
We just don't want you out here
looking foolish.

09:31.040 --> 09:33.000
- I'll stay off the dance floor.
- (laughs)

09:33.090 --> 09:34.420
GRANT: Vic. Hey.

09:34.500 --> 09:36.460
I'm sorry to interrupt, Mary, my bad,

09:36.540 --> 09:39.000
but, uh, Melinda's drunk

09:39.090 --> 09:40.670
and she's standing on top of my piano.

09:41.750 --> 09:43.540
- That concerns me.
- Yeah.

09:43.630 --> 09:45.250
- Whoo.
- (people cheering)

09:45.340 --> 09:46.590
MELINDA: I like dancing though.

09:46.670 --> 09:49.920
- You could dance if you want.
- (excited chatter)

09:50.000 --> 09:52.000
Ya, ya, ya. Okay, okay.

09:52.090 --> 09:53.380
I-I don't know how to give toasts,

09:53.460 --> 09:56.210
so I'm going to climb down from this piano

09:56.290 --> 09:58.790
and how about if I play a song.

09:58.880 --> 10:00.750
- (whoops, cheers)
- Yeah?

10:03.090 --> 10:05.250
My husband's good at giving toasts.

10:05.340 --> 10:07.340
- PARTYGOER: Yeah, Vic!
- (shouts, cheers)

10:08.920 --> 10:11.960
(plays gentle melody)

10:14.460 --> 10:16.710
MELINDA (laughing): Okay.

10:16.790 --> 10:18.380
Oh.

10:19.880 --> 10:22.420
(singing "Via Con Me" in Italian)

10:48.130 --> 10:51.630
(others joining in):
♪ It's wonderful, it's wonderful ♪

10:51.710 --> 10:53.630
♪ It's wonderful ♪

10:53.710 --> 10:55.960
♪ Good luck, my baby ♪

10:56.040 --> 10:59.290
♪ It's wonderful, it's wonderful ♪

10:59.380 --> 11:01.540
♪ It's wonderful ♪

11:01.630 --> 11:03.250
♪ I dream of you ♪

11:03.340 --> 11:06.380
♪ Chips, chips ♪

11:06.460 --> 11:09.670
♪ Doo, doo, doo-doo-doo,
ci-boom, ci-boom, boom ♪

11:09.750 --> 11:10.960
♪ Doo, doo, doo-doo-doo ♪

11:11.040 --> 11:13.380
♪ Ci-boom, ci-boom, boom ♪

11:13.460 --> 11:15.500
♪ Doo, doo, doo-doo-doo. ♪

11:17.960 --> 11:20.130
- (song ends)
- (whoops)

11:20.210 --> 11:21.710
(cheering, applause)

11:23.170 --> 11:25.090
♪ Chips, chips ♪

11:25.170 --> 11:27.340
Whoo! ♪ Doo, doo, doo-doo-doo ♪

11:27.420 --> 11:29.210
♪ Ci-boom, ci-boom, boom. ♪

11:29.290 --> 11:31.040
- WOMAN: Yes!
- (cheering)

11:32.130 --> 11:33.630
- Thanks so much.
- No problem.

11:33.710 --> 11:35.130
Good to see you, Vic.

11:35.210 --> 11:38.380
Hey, uh, two of those St-Germains
with the champagne drink things.

11:38.460 --> 11:40.000
BARTENDER:
Got you right there, boss.

11:40.090 --> 11:41.670
- Thank you.
- BARTENDER: No problem.

11:41.750 --> 11:43.290
How you doin', Vic?

11:43.380 --> 11:45.670
I'm fine. How are you?

11:45.750 --> 11:47.540
Eh, hangin' in there, bro.

11:54.340 --> 11:57.130
I just want to tell you two things, okay?

11:57.210 --> 11:58.630
Okay.

11:58.710 --> 12:01.630
I really want to repay you
for your abundant hospitality,

12:01.710 --> 12:03.210
you and your wife,

12:03.290 --> 12:06.590
as, you know, a stranger to the area.

12:06.670 --> 12:08.790
Sure.

12:08.880 --> 12:10.250
You've both been really cool.

12:10.340 --> 12:11.960
Really cool.

12:13.380 --> 12:15.040
The second?

12:15.130 --> 12:16.250
Huh?

12:16.340 --> 12:18.380
- The second thing you wanted to...
- Oh, man.

12:18.460 --> 12:19.880
I wanted to say, you're a brick

12:19.960 --> 12:22.670
for how nice you are
about me seeing your wife.

12:22.750 --> 12:25.790
(short laugh) Seeing my wife.

12:27.670 --> 12:30.090
It's good to have a friend.

12:33.840 --> 12:35.840
I mean, it's all innocent, of course,
you know,

12:35.920 --> 12:39.340
but some guys, some husbands,

12:39.420 --> 12:41.670
- they get a little…
- Yeah, jealous.

12:41.750 --> 12:43.540
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

12:43.630 --> 12:47.380
Have you been around here long enough
where you've heard the name Martin McRae?

12:47.460 --> 12:50.710
Uh, the guy…
yeah, the guy who's gone missing.

12:50.790 --> 12:53.040
He saw a lot of my wife.

12:55.090 --> 12:56.790
What does that mean?

12:56.880 --> 12:59.540
He started seeing a lot of my wife.

13:02.670 --> 13:04.380
You suggesting…?

13:05.460 --> 13:07.210
They were friends.

13:10.210 --> 13:13.630
You want me to believe
you did something to Martin McRae?

13:15.340 --> 13:17.500
I killed him.

13:22.500 --> 13:24.170
Does Melinda know?

13:24.250 --> 13:25.670
Oh, God, no.

13:25.750 --> 13:27.420
She'd be horrified.

13:29.750 --> 13:31.840
All right, bro,

13:31.920 --> 13:33.290
considering he was a friend of yours,

13:33.380 --> 13:35.750
I don't think it's very funny
to joke about...

13:35.840 --> 13:38.040
He wasn't a friend of mine.

13:38.130 --> 13:39.540
A friend of your wife's.

13:39.630 --> 13:40.880
(chuckles): Well...

13:40.960 --> 13:43.210
that's obviously something different,
isn't it?

13:46.290 --> 13:48.170
Are you, like, threatening me?

13:48.250 --> 13:50.630
Do you feel threatened?

13:53.750 --> 13:55.290
I don't believe you.

13:55.380 --> 13:57.670
Then don't.

14:02.540 --> 14:05.290
- ("Dancing on My Own" by Robyn plays)
- (crowd chatter)

14:08.750 --> 14:09.880
I'll be right back.

14:09.960 --> 14:11.000
Joel?

14:14.960 --> 14:16.420
JOEL: I'm going home.

14:16.500 --> 14:17.960
- What?
- I'll call you tomorrow.

14:18.040 --> 14:19.380
MELINDA: What happened?

14:19.460 --> 14:21.960
♪ But I'm not the guy you're taking home ♪

14:22.040 --> 14:24.130
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

14:24.210 --> 14:28.210
♪ I keep dancing on my own ♪

14:28.290 --> 14:31.090
♪ I keep dancing on... ♪

14:31.170 --> 14:33.090
(music continues muffled)

14:33.170 --> 14:35.170
- (people cheering)
- (balloons popping)

14:38.880 --> 14:41.380
MELINDA:
What did you say to Joel?

14:41.460 --> 14:42.880
Nothing.

14:44.750 --> 14:46.750
(laughs)

14:47.590 --> 14:49.380
You must've said something.

14:49.460 --> 14:50.880
No.

14:50.960 --> 14:52.340
I didn't say anything.

14:55.920 --> 14:59.040
Well, I saw you talking.

14:59.130 --> 15:00.590
What were you talking about?

15:00.670 --> 15:02.670
Bedbugs, maybe? No, that was Mary.

15:04.090 --> 15:05.630
(Melinda sighs)

15:05.710 --> 15:07.630
You're so weird.

15:09.670 --> 15:11.420
Would you like to get in the car?

15:18.210 --> 15:21.170
You must've said something...

15:21.250 --> 15:24.170
'cause he was different
after he talked to you.

15:25.250 --> 15:28.540
I promise you, I didn't.

15:30.750 --> 15:32.920
I don't believe you.

15:43.880 --> 15:45.880
♪ ♪

16:07.170 --> 16:08.840
(door closes)

16:08.920 --> 16:10.500
VIC: So, uh...

16:10.590 --> 16:12.500
- five hours, right?
- CHELSEA: Yeah.

16:12.590 --> 16:14.340
- VIC: That's a hundred.
- Mm-hmm.

16:14.420 --> 16:16.790
- Venmo. I-I'll give you 200. How's that?
- Oh, sure.

16:16.880 --> 16:18.380
Melinda, what are you doing?

16:18.460 --> 16:21.090
- I'm gonna make coffee.
- I'll make you coffee.

16:21.170 --> 16:22.380
Go to bed. You're drunk.

16:22.460 --> 16:25.380
- I can do it.
- No, it's fine. I...

16:25.460 --> 16:28.420
Melinda… you're naked.

16:28.500 --> 16:29.500
What are you doing?

16:29.590 --> 16:32.040
- What?
- The babysitter's standing right there.

16:33.540 --> 16:35.090
- VIC: The babysitter.
- (Melinda scoffs)

16:35.170 --> 16:36.170
So what?

16:36.250 --> 16:38.670
- It's not appropriate.
- Jesus Christ.

16:38.750 --> 16:41.460
America is so suffocating.

16:41.540 --> 16:44.250
- (Melinda sighs)
- Sorry about that.

16:44.340 --> 16:47.250
- My wife's... a whole nother culture.
- Yeah, it's okay.

16:47.340 --> 16:49.130
(Melinda sighs)

16:52.380 --> 16:54.130
Thank you.

16:56.590 --> 17:00.290
I wish you'd pick someone
with some more brains.

17:02.340 --> 17:05.089
Is that what interests you in a woman?

17:06.170 --> 17:08.589
Her intelligence?

17:08.670 --> 17:11.839
That's one of the things, yes.

17:11.920 --> 17:13.920
Is that why you picked me?

17:14.000 --> 17:17.589
For my brains?

17:17.670 --> 17:19.750
You're very smart, Melinda.

17:19.839 --> 17:22.130
Yeah.

17:22.210 --> 17:25.130
Not in a way you respect.

17:30.380 --> 17:35.210
Joel might be dumb,
but me makes me enjoy who I am.

17:36.290 --> 17:38.840
(sighs) And that turns me on.

17:42.590 --> 17:44.460
♪ ♪

17:48.250 --> 17:50.000
Vic.

17:55.290 --> 17:57.840
Close the door on your way out.

17:59.380 --> 18:01.290
(crickets chirping)

18:01.380 --> 18:03.380
♪ ♪

18:06.420 --> 18:08.540
(misters spraying)

18:17.170 --> 18:19.170
♪ ♪

18:25.170 --> 18:27.170
♪ ♪

18:40.210 --> 18:42.210
♪ ♪

18:51.460 --> 18:53.710
(whirring)

19:00.710 --> 19:02.000
(pills rattle)

19:02.090 --> 19:03.920
Thank you.

19:07.790 --> 19:10.000
Stick with it, Trix.

19:16.000 --> 19:17.840
(toy whirring)

19:22.090 --> 19:25.460
Did you know I had it on there wrong?

19:28.000 --> 19:30.460
Were you going to tell me?

19:30.540 --> 19:32.290
I didn't need to tell you, did I?

19:34.500 --> 19:36.500
In no time, you'll be like your dad,

19:36.590 --> 19:38.420
building bombs.

19:38.500 --> 19:40.380
- (quietly): Hmm.
- (toy whirs)

19:40.460 --> 19:41.670
TRIXIE: Dad doesn't build bombs.

19:41.750 --> 19:44.460
He made a computer chip.

19:51.290 --> 19:52.540
("You Make Me Feel Like Dancing"
by Leo Sayer playing)

19:52.630 --> 19:55.710
♪ You've got a cute way of talking ♪

19:56.880 --> 20:00.670
♪ You've got the better of me ♪

20:01.880 --> 20:03.840
♪ Just hold me tight ♪

20:03.920 --> 20:06.290
♪ And leave on the light ♪

20:07.340 --> 20:10.840
♪ 'Cause I don't wanna go home ♪

20:12.040 --> 20:14.420
♪ You've put a spell on me ♪

20:14.500 --> 20:16.960
♪ I'm right where you want me to be ♪

20:17.040 --> 20:20.380
VIC and TRIXIE:
♪ You make me feel like dancing... ♪

20:20.460 --> 20:22.880
- VIC: So, you have music today, right?
- (kids chattering)

20:22.960 --> 20:24.210
TRIXIE: Yes.

20:24.290 --> 20:26.210
- VIC: Does that mean violin?
- Yes.

20:26.290 --> 20:27.710
- Will that be fun?
- Yes.

20:27.790 --> 20:28.880
VIC (chuckles): Okay.

20:28.960 --> 20:31.170
Have a good day. I love you!

20:31.250 --> 20:33.250
Love you!

20:34.880 --> 20:37.340
MAN: Your mom is gonna get you
after school, all right?

20:37.420 --> 20:39.000
CHILD: I'm coming!

20:39.090 --> 20:41.090
(chattering continues)

20:42.340 --> 20:43.710
KRISTIN: Vic!

20:43.790 --> 20:45.750
Vic!

20:47.540 --> 20:49.130
What?

20:49.210 --> 20:51.250
You're running around murdering people

20:51.340 --> 20:53.840
and you don't call me
to help cover up the crime scene?

20:53.920 --> 20:55.380
- It was a joke.
- Yeah.

20:55.460 --> 20:57.040
I should fucking hope so.

20:58.130 --> 20:59.210
How'd you hear about it?

20:59.290 --> 21:01.210
(sighs) I've heard about it
from so many people now,

21:01.290 --> 21:03.210
