01:06:50.460 --> 01:06:55.590
(vocalizing)

01:07:00.500 --> 01:07:02.380
(vocalizing)

01:07:13.380 --> 01:07:15.250
(panting)

01:07:15.340 --> 01:07:16.790
(sniffs)

01:07:16.880 --> 01:07:18.790
- (kids chattering)
- VIC: You sure?

01:07:18.880 --> 01:07:20.540
Okay.

01:07:20.630 --> 01:07:22.130
(lively chatter)

01:07:24.500 --> 01:07:26.170
I love you!

01:07:26.250 --> 01:07:28.170
Love you, too!

01:07:28.250 --> 01:07:30.170
KIDS: Love you!

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:37.340
Hi.

01:07:37.420 --> 01:07:39.380
I didn't know your kids went
to this school.

01:07:39.460 --> 01:07:40.790
They don't.

01:07:40.880 --> 01:07:44.880
I was actually hoping to talk to you
and I didn't want to come to the house,

01:07:44.960 --> 01:07:47.460
and, uh, I didn't know where else
to find you.

01:07:47.540 --> 01:07:49.710
Okay.

01:07:49.790 --> 01:07:54.630
I just want you to know that I don't
approve of what my husband's doing.

01:07:54.710 --> 01:07:56.500
What's he doing?

01:07:56.590 --> 01:08:00.000
I don't think that talking about people
behind their backs is right.

01:08:00.090 --> 01:08:02.210
- Neither do I.
- I mean, it's ridiculous

01:08:02.290 --> 01:08:05.380
for Don to keep insisting
that you could've...

01:08:05.460 --> 01:08:07.880
You know, with Mr. De Lisle's accident.

01:08:07.960 --> 01:08:10.000
And I told Don, I said,

01:08:10.090 --> 01:08:11.790
I don't think it's a good idea
to have Melinda over to the house,

01:08:11.880 --> 01:08:14.710
but he keeps inviting her over
to talk about his crazy theories.

01:08:14.790 --> 01:08:16.340
I see.

01:08:18.290 --> 01:08:20.380
Look, hey.

01:08:20.460 --> 01:08:22.460
This is not your fault.

01:08:22.540 --> 01:08:25.460
We should have you and Don
over for dinner.

01:08:26.630 --> 01:08:27.920
(quietly): Uh...

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:30.340
Hi.

01:08:32.090 --> 01:08:33.840
Come in.

01:08:33.920 --> 01:08:36.250
VIC: Hey, come on in.

01:08:36.340 --> 01:08:38.420
- MELINDA: I love them.
- Oh, thanks.

01:08:38.500 --> 01:08:40.090
- Kelly, you look so beautiful, I can't stand it.
- DON: Hi.

01:08:40.170 --> 01:08:41.540
KELLY: Oh, thank you, Vic.

01:08:41.630 --> 01:08:43.170
- Hi.
- Don, thanks for coming. Come on in.

01:08:43.250 --> 01:08:44.540
DON: Thanks for having us.

01:08:44.630 --> 01:08:46.250
VIC: This way.

01:08:46.340 --> 01:08:49.000
Do you know anything about snails, Don?

01:08:49.090 --> 01:08:50.420
I can't say I do.

01:08:50.500 --> 01:08:53.670
A snail will climb a 12-foot wall
to find its mate.

01:08:53.750 --> 01:08:56.210
- It's the smell.
- Huh.

01:08:56.290 --> 01:08:57.920
Mind if I smoke?

01:08:58.000 --> 01:08:59.840
Please don't... it'll kill 'em.

01:08:59.920 --> 01:09:02.420
Oh, well, we don't want that.

01:09:02.500 --> 01:09:08.290
Don, I need you to stop telling people
that I killed Charlie De Lisle.

01:09:08.380 --> 01:09:10.170
Is that right?

01:09:10.250 --> 01:09:11.750
(misters sputtering)

01:09:11.840 --> 01:09:14.500
Yes. I think it's hurting your reputation.

01:09:14.590 --> 01:09:16.840
I think it's hurting Kelly's reputation.

01:09:16.920 --> 01:09:20.250
Well, that's funny that you're not worried
it'll hurt yours.

01:09:26.250 --> 01:09:27.840
(Don groans)

01:09:29.250 --> 01:09:32.880
You know, I was gonna ask you
what you think killed Charlie.

01:09:32.960 --> 01:09:34.380
What killed him?

01:09:34.460 --> 01:09:36.380
Well, just, who dies like that?

01:09:36.460 --> 01:09:38.790
Accidentally in a swimming pool?

01:09:38.880 --> 01:09:41.340
Thousands of people a year.

01:09:42.380 --> 01:09:44.630
What do you think killed him?

01:09:44.710 --> 01:09:46.790
- I think you drowned him.
- Yeah?

01:09:46.880 --> 01:09:49.250
I heard I killed Martin McRae, too.

01:09:49.340 --> 01:09:50.630
(misters turn off)

01:09:50.710 --> 01:09:53.000
You said you killed him.

01:09:53.090 --> 01:09:54.420
Did you believe me?

01:09:54.500 --> 01:09:56.250
No.

01:09:56.340 --> 01:09:58.460
Good for you.

01:09:59.540 --> 01:10:01.840
I thought it was weird, though,
that you said you did,

01:10:01.920 --> 01:10:05.000
that you seemed to take pleasure in it.

01:10:05.090 --> 01:10:07.420
And that was enough for you
to share my wife's opinion?

01:10:07.500 --> 01:10:09.210
It's my opinion.

01:10:12.670 --> 01:10:13.670
(drill whirs)

01:10:20.340 --> 01:10:22.920
Would you, uh, be willing to take
a lie detector test

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:24.750
saying you didn't kill him?

01:10:24.840 --> 01:10:27.090
Sure. Get one.

01:10:30.540 --> 01:10:32.750
You're a weird guy.

01:10:32.840 --> 01:10:35.000
So I've been told.

01:10:37.960 --> 01:10:39.960
(people talking low, indistinctly nearby)

01:10:51.540 --> 01:10:53.540
♪ ♪

01:11:13.630 --> 01:11:15.630
♪ ♪

01:11:18.590 --> 01:11:19.920
Hey, hon.

01:11:22.340 --> 01:11:24.880
Hi.

01:11:24.960 --> 01:11:28.500
Um, we're having lunch.

01:11:28.590 --> 01:11:29.790
Oh.

01:11:29.880 --> 01:11:33.420
I was just going to get something to go,
but I can join you for a second.

01:11:34.500 --> 01:11:37.340
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:11:37.420 --> 01:11:39.460
This is my husband, Vic.

01:11:39.540 --> 01:11:41.090
- Victor Van Allen.
- Oh.

01:11:41.170 --> 01:11:43.920
- It's, uh, nice to meet you.
- You, too.

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:45.170
This is David Ricigliani.

01:11:45.250 --> 01:11:47.210
He's opening a practice here.

01:11:47.290 --> 01:11:49.290
Oh. What kind of practice?

01:11:49.380 --> 01:11:52.040
- Psychotherapy.
- (laughs softly)

01:11:52.130 --> 01:11:54.040
Well, this town definitely needs that.

01:11:54.130 --> 01:11:55.790
- You think?
- First practice?

01:11:55.880 --> 01:11:56.960
Uh, no, no.

01:11:57.040 --> 01:11:59.460
I actually closed my practice
in Cheshire recently.

01:11:59.540 --> 01:12:01.670
- Upgraded.
- Yeah.

01:12:01.750 --> 01:12:06.090
I'm curious, do you think my wife
has schizophrenic tendencies?

01:12:07.090 --> 01:12:08.750
- What?
- Well, he's a professional.

01:12:08.840 --> 01:12:10.420
I thought I'd ask.

01:12:10.500 --> 01:12:11.670
No.

01:12:11.750 --> 01:12:14.040
It's possible he may have some insight
as to… -You're such an asshole.

01:12:14.130 --> 01:12:15.630
- No, I don't think so at all.
- Hmm.

01:12:15.710 --> 01:12:19.040
Do you think my husband might be
psychopathic for asking you that?

01:12:19.130 --> 01:12:21.250
Or maybe just an asshole?

01:12:21.340 --> 01:12:23.000
(David laughs nervously)

01:12:23.090 --> 01:12:26.290
Uh… how about, uh, couples therapy?

01:12:26.380 --> 01:12:28.290
(Melinda laughing)

01:12:28.380 --> 01:12:31.880
I was going to get something to go for the
guys, but maybe I'll just skip it, huh?

01:12:31.960 --> 01:12:33.460
- Hate to interrupt your lunch.
- (Melinda laughs)

01:12:33.540 --> 01:12:35.630
MELINDA: I'm used to this.

01:12:37.880 --> 01:12:39.880
Nice to make your acquaintance, David.

01:12:39.960 --> 01:12:41.750
You don't happen to have a card, do you?

01:12:41.840 --> 01:12:44.670
'Cause I may need a psychotherapist.

01:12:44.750 --> 01:12:46.880
Oh, uh...

01:12:46.960 --> 01:12:49.840
No, no. I… I don't have any on me.

01:12:49.920 --> 01:12:51.710
VIC: Mm-hmm.

01:12:51.790 --> 01:12:54.500
Well, I know where to find you.

01:12:59.250 --> 01:13:01.920
(laughing)

01:13:03.000 --> 01:13:05.130
(low conversation)

01:13:06.210 --> 01:13:07.460
Hi.

01:13:08.540 --> 01:13:10.250
- Oh.
- Oh, I'm sorry to interrupt.

01:13:10.340 --> 01:13:12.210
I didn't know it was dinnertime, but...

01:13:12.290 --> 01:13:13.540
No, no, no, no, sit down, please.

01:13:13.630 --> 01:13:15.460
This will just take a second.

01:13:15.540 --> 01:13:16.670
Hi.

01:13:18.040 --> 01:13:19.960
I just have a question for Don.

01:13:20.040 --> 01:13:23.170
You know a guy named David Ricigliani?

01:13:24.130 --> 01:13:25.630
Um...

01:13:25.710 --> 01:13:27.630
Who's David Ricigliani?

01:13:27.710 --> 01:13:29.000
VIC:
He's a man your husband hired.

01:13:29.090 --> 01:13:30.290
Who did you hire?

01:13:30.380 --> 01:13:31.670
A private investigator.

01:13:31.750 --> 01:13:33.340
What for?

01:13:33.420 --> 01:13:34.590
To follow me.

01:13:34.670 --> 01:13:36.670
This is ridiculous.

01:13:36.750 --> 01:13:38.630
- How could you do that, Don?
- I made him a week ago.

01:13:38.710 --> 01:13:40.540
I ran into him at a diner with Melinda.

01:13:40.630 --> 01:13:43.290
Go outside, I see a telephoto lens
in the back of his car.

01:13:43.380 --> 01:13:44.590
Oh, my God.

01:13:44.670 --> 01:13:46.590
Guy tried to tell me
he was a psychotherapist.

01:13:46.670 --> 01:13:48.210
Where'd you find this guy?

01:13:48.290 --> 01:13:51.670
You can't just walk into my house
and accuse me, in front of my family...

01:13:51.750 --> 01:13:54.670
Apparently, anybody can accuse
anyone of anything.

01:13:54.750 --> 01:13:57.590
Unlike you, however, Don, I have proof.

01:13:57.670 --> 01:14:01.000
This is a bank record of a wire
from my wife

01:14:01.090 --> 01:14:05.540
to your account for $743.50,
which is sort of an unusual amount,

01:14:05.630 --> 01:14:07.500
so I assume you went splitsies
on the retainer.

01:14:07.590 --> 01:14:08.840
- Your wife…
- KELLY: Oh, my God.

01:14:08.920 --> 01:14:10.380
KELLY: Have you lost your mind?

01:14:10.460 --> 01:14:11.790
What the fuck were you thinking, Don?

01:14:11.880 --> 01:14:13.340
Goldie, go inside.

01:14:13.420 --> 01:14:16.420
- Uh, this is, this is humiliating.
- At least tell me where you found him.

01:14:16.500 --> 01:14:18.880
Your wife wired that money to me.

01:14:18.960 --> 01:14:20.040
- Back of a newspaper?
- KELLY: Goldie, I said inside.

01:14:20.130 --> 01:14:21.540
It's from your wife.

01:14:21.630 --> 01:14:23.210
- VIC: Sorry to interrupt your dinner.
- KELLY: No, no, no.

01:14:23.290 --> 01:14:24.540
Don't you apologize for anything.

01:14:24.630 --> 01:14:26.500
I'm the one who's sorry.

01:14:26.590 --> 01:14:27.960
What the hell are you apologizing
to him for?

01:14:28.040 --> 01:14:29.090
Are you kidding me, Don?

01:14:29.170 --> 01:14:31.750
- Don't apologize to this piece of shit.
- Will you stop, Don?

01:14:31.840 --> 01:14:33.290
Goldie, I thought I told you to go inside.

01:14:33.380 --> 01:14:36.000
She did tell you to go inside.
Go inside, Goldie.

01:14:36.090 --> 01:14:37.670
Go inside, Goldie!

01:14:37.750 --> 01:14:40.040
Goddamn it.
Who left the fucking gate open?

01:14:41.090 --> 01:14:43.090
♪ ♪

01:15:04.630 --> 01:15:06.630
(talking low, indistinctly)

01:15:21.790 --> 01:15:23.250
TONY (laughs): Hey.

01:15:23.340 --> 01:15:24.670
(kisses)

01:15:32.500 --> 01:15:34.500
(burbling)

01:15:36.630 --> 01:15:38.460
- TRIXIE: Daddy?
- VIC: Mm-hmm.

01:15:38.540 --> 01:15:40.500
When Charlie drowned in the swimming pool,

01:15:40.590 --> 01:15:42.790
did his feet touch the bottom?

01:15:42.880 --> 01:15:44.630
I don't know. I wasn't there.

01:15:44.710 --> 01:15:46.750
Sure, you were there.

01:15:46.840 --> 01:15:49.920
Well, I was there when we were trying
to save him...

01:15:50.000 --> 01:15:53.500
Everyone was...
but everything happened very quickly.

01:15:53.590 --> 01:15:56.790
But you still know what you did.

01:15:56.880 --> 01:15:59.130
I didn't do it, honey.

01:15:59.210 --> 01:16:01.840
I think you're kidding me.

01:16:01.920 --> 01:16:04.420
VIC: I'm not.

01:16:04.500 --> 01:16:06.920
I'm not, Trix.

01:16:07.960 --> 01:16:09.130
(burbling)

01:16:09.210 --> 01:16:11.420
Why won't you tell me how you did it?

01:16:11.500 --> 01:16:14.290
Everyone keeps asking me how you did it.

01:16:20.250 --> 01:16:21.960
Sweetheart...

01:16:23.040 --> 01:16:25.170
...if I did kill someone...

01:16:26.250 --> 01:16:28.380
...do you know what they would do to me?

01:16:28.460 --> 01:16:33.840
They would put me in prison
for the rest of my life.

01:16:33.920 --> 01:16:36.040
Do you understand?

01:16:40.090 --> 01:16:41.960
I still think you drowned him.

01:16:42.040 --> 01:16:44.840
You're just telling me you didn't.

01:16:47.670 --> 01:16:50.710
Well, let's keep that between us.

01:16:50.790 --> 01:16:52.750
(burbling)

01:16:52.840 --> 01:16:55.380
(tapping)

01:16:56.670 --> 01:16:58.090
TRIXIE: Rita.

01:17:00.090 --> 01:17:02.170
Kangaroo.

01:17:03.540 --> 01:17:05.710
Bring sloth back in.

01:17:05.790 --> 01:17:07.540
(phone ringing)

01:17:07.630 --> 01:17:09.670
TRIXIE: You, you?

01:17:09.750 --> 01:17:11.790
(Trixie chuckles, talks indistinctly)

01:17:15.130 --> 01:17:16.380
MELINDA (quietly): Yes?

01:17:18.630 --> 01:17:20.960
(Melinda groans)

01:17:21.040 --> 01:17:23.210
It's killing me.

01:17:23.290 --> 01:17:24.960
What?

01:17:25.040 --> 01:17:26.670
Brazil?

01:17:26.750 --> 01:17:29.090
(gasps)
I've never been to Brazil.

01:17:29.170 --> 01:17:30.880
(Trixie singing
"Old MacDonald Had a Farm" indistinctly)

01:17:30.960 --> 01:17:32.630
MELINDA (quietly): Yes.

01:17:34.790 --> 01:17:37.000
No, she would.

01:17:37.090 --> 01:17:38.750
She'd love it.

01:17:39.840 --> 01:17:41.590
She'll get used to it.

01:17:44.040 --> 01:17:46.340
What'd you say?

01:17:46.420 --> 01:17:49.130
Oh, we can talk.

01:17:50.250 --> 01:17:52.340
Love you.

01:17:52.420 --> 01:17:54.790
(wood creaking)

01:18:05.250 --> 01:18:07.250
♪ ♪

01:18:12.500 --> 01:18:14.210
VIC: How was your night?

01:18:19.090 --> 01:18:20.960
You don't want to tell me?

01:18:27.420 --> 01:18:29.960
You just don't want to talk.

01:18:46.920 --> 01:18:48.920
(misters spraying)

01:18:57.920 --> 01:18:59.540
- You must be Vic.
- Yeah.

01:18:59.630 --> 01:19:01.000
- Tony Cameron.
- Hi.

01:19:01.090 --> 01:19:02.340
Old friend of Melinda's.

01:19:02.420 --> 01:19:03.920
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

01:19:04.000 --> 01:19:06.210
- Thank you for having me over.
- Sure.

01:19:06.290 --> 01:19:08.630
- Nice space you got here.
- Thank you very much.

01:19:08.710 --> 01:19:10.340
Yeah, it's like a science lab.

01:19:10.420 --> 01:19:12.040
(laughs softly) Kind of.

01:19:13.130 --> 01:19:14.380
Are those snails?

01:19:14.460 --> 01:19:16.340
Yeah. Check it out.

01:19:16.420 --> 01:19:18.460
TONY: Wow.

01:19:18.540 --> 01:19:19.790
How about that?

01:19:19.880 --> 01:19:22.210
Huh.

01:19:28.000 --> 01:19:29.880
Um, is Melinda here?

01:19:29.960 --> 01:19:31.380
Yeah, she's upstairs.

01:19:31.460 --> 01:19:33.420
All right.

01:19:33.500 --> 01:19:35.840
All right, well,
I guess I'll see you up there.

01:19:35.920 --> 01:19:37.290
- Great.
- Okay.

01:19:41.670 --> 01:19:45.090
TONY: Yeah, so I've been working on,
uh, building LEED-certified housing.

01:19:45.170 --> 01:19:46.420
- Oh.
- Yeah.

01:19:46.500 --> 01:19:49.170
In both-both here in the States
and-and also in Brazil, actually.

01:19:49.250 --> 01:19:51.170
That's where our new initiative is.

01:19:51.250 --> 01:19:56.290
'Cause, you know, the point is, well,
if we can create sustainable living spaces

01:19:56.380 --> 01:19:59.710
for people around the world, we can help
create a more sustainable planet.

01:19:59.790 --> 01:20:02.380
You know, for-for… for Trixie.

01:20:02.460 --> 01:20:04.590
You know, for the,
for the next generation.

01:20:04.670 --> 01:20:06.500
Can I get you a drink?

01:20:06.590 --> 01:20:08.500
I'll take a sparkling water,
if you got it.

01:20:08.590 --> 01:20:09.750
VIC: Sure.

01:20:09.840 --> 01:20:10.920
TONY: Thank you.

01:20:13.040 --> 01:20:14.040
(laughs): Hi.

01:20:15.130 --> 01:20:17.250
- Hi. (chuckles)
- Hi.

01:20:17.340 --> 01:20:19.130
- There you are.
- Tony.

01:20:19.210 --> 01:20:21.420
- Hi.
- Hi. Wow, it's great to see you.

01:20:21.500 --> 01:20:22.880
- Hola.
- Hola.

01:20:22.960 --> 01:20:24.040
Hi. (laughs)

01:20:24.130 --> 01:20:25.250
¿Cómo estás?

01:20:25.340 --> 01:20:26.460
I can't believe you're here.

01:20:26.540 --> 01:20:28.380
- I know, it's been a while.
- It's just crazy.

01:20:28.460 --> 01:20:30.420
I know.

01:20:30.500 --> 01:20:32.040
How are you?

01:20:32.130 --> 01:20:34.540
I'm great. I'm great. Great.

01:20:34.630 --> 01:20:36.090
You hungry?

01:20:36.170 --> 01:20:37.500
Yeah, actually, I'm starving.

01:20:37.590 --> 01:20:39.710
I'm starving. Well, that's why
I came over, obviously.

01:20:39.790 --> 01:20:41.710
- Starving's good.
- Yeah.

01:20:41.790 --> 01:20:43.210
VIC: Here you go.

01:20:43.290 --> 01:20:44.290
Thank you.

01:20:44.380 --> 01:20:45.790
Can I help?

01:20:45.880 --> 01:20:47.130
- No.
- No?

01:20:47.210 --> 01:20:48.630
- No.
- All right.

01:20:50.540 --> 01:20:51.670
MELINDA: Is he being nice?

01:20:51.750 --> 01:20:52.790
He's very nice. Very nice.

01:20:52.880 --> 01:20:54.170
I was just telling him how we reconnected.

01:20:54.250 --> 01:20:55.880
I was, I was working in
the state legislature here

01:20:55.960 --> 01:20:58.500
and we started just chatting on Facebook.

01:20:58.590 --> 01:21:00.500
I think what you're doing
is very inspiring.

01:21:00.590 --> 01:21:01.670
Well, thank you.

01:21:01.750 --> 01:21:03.420
- If that counts.
- Thank you.

01:21:03.500 --> 01:21:04.750
- Right?
- I'm just...

01:21:04.840 --> 01:21:05.880
- Very admirable.
- MELINDA: Yeah.

01:21:05.960 --> 01:21:09.540
Just, I'm happy it gives me a chance
to reconnect with old friends.

01:21:09.630 --> 01:21:13.000
Fun fact: Tony was the first American
I fucked.

01:21:15.630 --> 01:21:17.540
(laughs nervously)

01:21:17.630 --> 01:21:19.250
- MELINDA: What? You blushing?
- TONY: Just...

01:21:19.340 --> 01:21:20.920
TONY (laughing):
Well, it's just…

01:21:21.000 --> 01:21:23.170
- MELINDA: Are you okay?
- (both laughing)

01:21:23.250 --> 01:21:25.960
It's just an unnecessary amount of detail,
Melinda.

01:21:26.040 --> 01:21:28.210
Well, it's true. What?

01:21:29.710 --> 01:21:31.000
Wha...? Don't worry about Vic.

01:21:31.090 --> 01:21:32.960
- He couldn't care less.
- Oh.

01:21:33.040 --> 01:21:36.710
He's doesn't want to control me
like a normal man.

01:21:36.790 --> 01:21:38.590
Uh, no, I'm not normal.

01:21:38.670 --> 01:21:41.790
TONY: As somebody who dated her, Vic,
I-I really sympathize with you.

01:21:41.880 --> 01:21:43.750
She's-she's a very difficult person

01:21:43.840 --> 01:21:46.210
- to control.
- Oh, yeah. Right?

01:21:46.290 --> 01:21:48.500
But that's also what makes her special.

01:21:48.590 --> 01:21:50.670
You know that.

01:21:52.000 --> 01:21:54.210
And then you broke up with me.

01:21:54.290 --> 01:21:56.000
- Did I?
- Yes, you did.

01:21:56.090 --> 01:21:58.500
He broke my heart.

01:21:59.590 --> 01:22:02.290
- TONY: It's not true.
- MELINDA: You did, too.

01:22:02.380 --> 01:22:04.130
TONY:
Smells great over here, by the way.

01:22:04.210 --> 01:22:06.380
- MELINDA: Thank you, thank you, thank you.
- TONY: Yeah.

01:22:06.460 --> 01:22:07.540
Mmm.

01:22:07.630 --> 01:22:09.960
Vic, you know what we should do
is get some-some snails.

01:22:10.040 --> 01:22:11.420
(gasps)

01:22:11.500 --> 01:22:13.460
That sounds amazing.

01:22:13.540 --> 01:22:14.960
Garlic and a little butter?

01:22:15.040 --> 01:22:16.380
- Want me to get 'em? I can get 'em.
- Come on.

01:22:16.460 --> 01:22:18.920
No, the snails aren't for eating.

01:22:20.250 --> 01:22:22.040
Oh, sorry. They're not for eat...

01:22:22.130 --> 01:22:23.500
What are they, what are they for?

01:22:23.590 --> 01:22:25.750
They're not for anything.

01:22:25.840 --> 01:22:27.880
TONY: Well, you won't miss
a dozen or so, will you?

01:22:27.960 --> 01:22:29.210
The snails are not for eating.

01:22:29.290 --> 01:22:30.790
MELINDA:
No, he won't. Just go get them.

01:22:30.880 --> 01:22:33.750
I mean, they're-they're not like
your pets, are they? (laughs)

01:22:33.840 --> 01:22:35.790
Fun fact:

01:22:35.880 --> 01:22:38.630
You know you have to starve them, right?

01:22:38.710 --> 01:22:39.960
TONY: What?

01:22:40.040 --> 01:22:42.750
Before you eat them, you have to make
sure their intestines are empty.

01:22:42.840 --> 01:22:46.460
Otherwise, you'll poison yourself
and you'll die.

01:22:49.710 --> 01:22:51.880
I did not know that.

01:22:51.960 --> 01:22:53.670
No snails.

01:22:53.750 --> 01:22:54.960
(chuckles softly)

01:22:55.040 --> 01:22:57.210
Who knew?

01:22:57.290 --> 01:22:59.210
("La Murga" by Willie Colon, Hector Levoe,
Yomo Toro playing loudly)

01:22:59.290 --> 01:23:01.290
(Tony and Melinda talking indistinctly)

01:23:04.040 --> 01:23:06.500
(music and talking continue)

01:23:06.590 --> 01:23:08.750
(Melinda laughing)

01:23:14.130 --> 01:23:16.130
(music continues playing)

01:23:35.340 --> 01:23:37.340
♪ ♪

01:23:40.670 --> 01:23:42.670
(dialogue indistinct under music)

01:23:49.880 --> 01:23:51.880
(music continues in distance)

01:24:09.040 --> 01:24:11.040
(song fades)

01:24:19.460 --> 01:24:21.460
♪ ♪

01:24:37.500 --> 01:24:39.500
(birds chirping)

01:24:54.540 --> 01:24:56.460
Hey, Tony.

01:24:56.540 --> 01:24:58.500
Oh, Vic. That's funny.

01:24:58.590 --> 01:25:00.000
Melinda's been trying to get a hold of you.

01:25:00.090 --> 01:25:01.500
She's got a building site
she wants to show you.

01:25:01.590 --> 01:25:02.840
She keeps talking about it.

01:25:02.920 --> 01:25:05.540
Oh, really? She didn't, uh, say anything.

01:25:05.630 --> 01:25:07.670
Well, come on, jump in.

01:25:08.750 --> 01:25:10.750
All right.

01:25:21.540 --> 01:25:23.460
It's really a beautiful spot.

01:25:23.540 --> 01:25:26.420
Melinda and I used to go hiking up there
back when we started dating.

01:25:26.500 --> 01:25:28.380
Sounds nice.

01:25:30.420 --> 01:25:32.130
So why'd you break up with her?

01:25:32.210 --> 01:25:33.590
(engine accelerating)

01:25:35.210 --> 01:25:36.590
What?

01:25:36.670 --> 01:25:39.210
You know, when you guys were young.

01:25:39.290 --> 01:25:40.590
Oh.

01:25:40.670 --> 01:25:42.090
You know, I really don't remember.

01:25:42.170 --> 01:25:43.880
I… (clears throat)
It was such a long time ago.

01:25:43.960 --> 01:25:45.540
(tires screech)

01:25:46.630 --> 01:25:48.630
(engine accelerating)

01:26:01.460 --> 01:26:03.130
(thumps)

01:26:03.210 --> 01:26:04.670
(Tony clears throat)

01:26:04.750 --> 01:26:07.460
Going a little fast, Vic, don't you think?

01:26:07.540 --> 01:26:10.210
So you guys just, like, reconnected?

01:26:10.290 --> 01:26:14.710
Uh, yeah. I mean, a couple months ago,
just casually.

01:26:14.790 --> 01:26:16.540
You gonna be in town for a while?

01:26:20.790 --> 01:26:22.920
(exhales)

01:26:26.170 --> 01:26:27.920
This is the way, huh?

01:26:28.000 --> 01:26:29.340
Yep.

01:26:30.380 --> 01:26:32.590
Should I give Melinda a call?

01:26:32.670 --> 01:26:34.290
Sure, go ahead.

01:26:34.380 --> 01:26:36.920
(thumping)

01:26:38.000 --> 01:26:39.500
There's no service.

01:26:39.590 --> 01:26:41.040
Oh, that's right. I forgot.

01:26:48.710 --> 01:26:50.540
Here we are.

01:26:54.840 --> 01:26:57.170
(turns off engine)

01:26:57.250 --> 01:26:59.540
(Tony sighs)

01:27:01.960 --> 01:27:03.920
Where's Melinda?

01:27:04.000 --> 01:27:06.250
She and I used to go mountain biking
up here.

01:27:09.880 --> 01:27:11.670
There's a gorge just across the way.

01:27:13.630 --> 01:27:15.250
(grunts):
She said we should meet her there.

01:27:15.340 --> 01:27:16.790
(cries out)

01:27:16.880 --> 01:27:18.210
(groans): Ah, fuck.

01:27:18.290 --> 01:27:20.590
Oh, fuck.

01:27:22.420 --> 01:27:23.630
(groans)

01:27:23.710 --> 01:27:25.040
(panting)

01:27:25.130 --> 01:27:26.790
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

01:27:26.880 --> 01:27:28.210
- Stop, stop.
- (grunting)

01:27:28.290 --> 01:27:30.170
(yells)

01:27:30.250 --> 01:27:31.880
(screams)

01:27:33.420 --> 01:27:34.920
(grunting, whimpering)

01:27:41.920 --> 01:27:43.920
(panting)

01:28:18.710 --> 01:28:20.710
(breathing heavily)

01:28:27.590 --> 01:28:28.840
(sneezes)

01:28:29.920 --> 01:28:31.920
♪ ♪

01:28:33.540 --> 01:28:35.540
(strained grunting)

01:28:51.420 --> 01:28:53.420
(panting)

01:29:25.540 --> 01:29:27.540
♪ ♪

01:29:51.960 --> 01:29:53.960
♪ ♪

01:29:59.000 --> 01:30:01.000
(Melinda laughing distantly)

01:30:03.210 --> 01:30:04.290
(laughing)

01:30:04.380 --> 01:30:07.380
- (Trixie squeals, giggles)
- Here? (mutters)

01:30:07.460 --> 01:30:09.540
- (door opens, closes)
- You're gonna fall.

01:30:09.630 --> 01:30:12.750
- (laughing): You're gonna fall.
- (Trixie laughs)

01:30:12.840 --> 01:30:14.340
What are you guys doing?

01:30:14.420 --> 01:30:17.590
(laughing)

01:30:18.670 --> 01:30:19.960
How's Tony?

01:30:20.040 --> 01:30:21.750
- MELINDA: Right here?
- TRIXIE: Mm-hmm.

01:30:22.840 --> 01:30:24.670
I don't know.

01:30:25.750 --> 01:30:28.790
I like him. He's actually got brains.

01:30:30.340 --> 01:30:31.710
(laughs softly)

01:30:35.790 --> 01:30:39.790
I'm going to pour you just a glass,
'cause we're celebrating.

01:30:40.880 --> 01:30:42.710
Now we toast.

01:30:42.790 --> 01:30:48.130
May the boys of St. Vincent's
keep their hands off our pigtails.

01:30:52.460 --> 01:30:54.290
What are you doing?

01:30:54.380 --> 01:30:56.340
You getting her drunk?

01:30:56.420 --> 01:30:58.130
VIC: We're celebrating.

01:30:58.210 --> 01:31:00.380
What are you celebrating?

01:31:00.460 --> 01:31:03.000
Oh, life.

01:31:03.090 --> 01:31:04.540
Wine.

01:31:07.340 --> 01:31:10.090
Have you seen him?

01:31:10.170 --> 01:31:12.130
Who?

01:31:12.210 --> 01:31:13.920
Tony.

01:31:14.000 --> 01:31:16.920
- VIC: Tony.
- Tony Pony!

01:31:17.000 --> 01:31:19.710
- VIC: Tony Pony?
- Tony Maloney!

01:31:19.790 --> 01:31:22.040
Tony Baloney, I have not seen.

01:31:25.340 --> 01:31:27.340
♪ ♪

01:31:54.790 --> 01:31:56.460
TRIXIE: Daddy?

01:31:56.540 --> 01:31:58.250
Yes.

01:31:58.340 --> 01:32:00.290
We're going on a picnic.

01:32:02.380 --> 01:32:04.880
Do you want to come with us?

01:32:04.960 --> 01:32:06.630
I would love to. Where we going?

01:32:06.710 --> 01:32:08.710
The gorge.

01:32:10.210 --> 01:32:12.750
The gorge?

01:32:12.840 --> 01:32:14.880
(birds chirping)

01:32:18.540 --> 01:32:20.540
(chuckling)

01:32:31.630 --> 01:32:34.920
Why are you the only man
who wants to stay with me?

01:32:36.460 --> 01:32:38.170
I don't know.

01:32:42.960 --> 01:32:45.250
But you do?

01:32:45.340 --> 01:32:47.540
I do.

01:33:03.130 --> 01:33:04.250
(Vic exhales)

01:33:14.090 --> 01:33:15.880
You're not bored?

01:33:15.960 --> 01:33:17.920
(breathlessly): No.

01:33:19.670 --> 01:33:21.590
Are you?

01:33:28.090 --> 01:33:30.920
But I'm sad.

01:33:34.170 --> 01:33:35.750
I got you something.

01:33:51.210 --> 01:33:53.210
♪ ♪

01:34:19.420 --> 01:34:22.090
You didn't know I took that.

01:34:26.840 --> 01:34:29.920
- I was three months pregnant.
- Mm-hmm.

01:34:39.840 --> 01:34:41.920
Thank you.

01:34:45.130 --> 01:34:46.960
(laughs softly)

01:34:51.500 --> 01:34:53.670
TRIXIE: Roger!

01:34:53.750 --> 01:34:56.340
- Hey, Trixie!
- Roger!

01:34:56.420 --> 01:34:57.790
Trix!

01:34:57.880 --> 01:34:59.210
- Hold on. Hold on.
- She's fine, she's fine.

01:34:59.290 --> 01:35:00.540
- (laughing): I'll be right back.
- Stay.

01:35:00.630 --> 01:35:02.960
- Trix! Uh...
- Vic, stay.

01:35:03.040 --> 01:35:06.000
Trixie, back up, honey.
Get away from the edge, sweet pea.

01:35:06.090 --> 01:35:07.460
Back up, back up, back up.

01:35:07.540 --> 01:35:09.960
(breathlessly): Thank you. Okay.

01:35:10.040 --> 01:35:11.460
We have to go back, okay?

01:35:11.540 --> 01:35:13.590
This is too close to the edge.

01:35:14.630 --> 01:35:16.630
♪ ♪

01:35:28.750 --> 01:35:30.670
- Let's go.
- Okay.

01:35:30.750 --> 01:35:32.790
Okay.

01:35:35.920 --> 01:35:37.920
♪ ♪

01:35:38.920 --> 01:35:41.540
Oh, damn. I left my scarf up there.

01:35:41.630 --> 01:35:43.750
- I'm sorry.
- (sighs)

01:35:43.840 --> 01:35:45.500
We can't go back now.

01:35:45.590 --> 01:35:47.460
Oh, I'll go back for it.

01:35:47.540 --> 01:35:49.290
But like tomorrow.

01:35:49.380 --> 01:35:51.880
